# IT Ops Dashboard Deployment Config

## Ports (DO NOT CHANGE)

| App | Port | URL |
|-----|------|-----|
| Production (itops-api) | 5005 | https://itopsconsole.com |
| Staging (itops-staging) | 5006 | https://staging.itopsconsole.com |

Nginx proxies each domain to its port. Changing ports breaks the site.

## Databases

- **Production**: `it_ops_dashboard`
- **Staging**: `it_ops_staging_db`

## PM2

- `pm2 restart` does NOT re-read `.env` — it reuses stored env.
- When `.env` or `.env.staging` changes: use `pm2 delete <app>` then `pm2 start ecosystem.config.cjs --only <app>`.

## Deploy Steps

1. `git pull && npm install && npm run build`
2. Staging: `pm2 restart itops-staging --update-env`
3. Test staging at https://staging.itopsconsole.com
4. Production: `pm2 restart itops-api --update-env`

## Environment Variables

See `.env.example` for the full list. Key required vars:
- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string (different per environment)
- `SESSION_SECRET` — Random string, min 32 chars (different per environment)
- `PORT` — 5005 (prod) or 5006 (staging)

## Git Workflow

- Single branch: `main`
- Push from Cursor → GitHub → pull on server
- Always deploy to staging first, then production
